description: The user clicked on the desktop, which opened a context menu with options such as "Arrange Icons By", "Refresh", "New", and "Properties".
outcome: A context menu appeared on the desktop, offering options like "Arrange Icons By", "Refresh", "New", and "Properties". The mouse cursor is no longer visible.

description: The user clicked the mouse to select "Properties" from the desktop context menu.
outcome: The context menu closed and the "Screen Saver" dropdown menu, previously showing "Properties", now displays "Windows XP".

description: The user clicked the "Screen Saver" dropdown menu, changing the selection from "Windows XP" to "Starfield".
outcome: The "Screen Saver" dropdown menu switched its selection from "Windows XP" to "Starfield."  Concurrently, the "Wait" text field and the "On resume, password protect" checkbox were removed.

description: The user clicked on the "None" option within the open "Screen Saver" dropdown menu of the "Display Properties" window.  As a result, the "Screen Saver" dropdown menu closed.
outcome: A new window, titled "Power Options Properties," opened on top of the "Display Properties" window.  The "Screen Saver" dropdown menu and the "Power..." button below it are no longer visible.

description: The user clicked the "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu and selected "Never".
outcome: The "Turn off monitor" setting in the dropdown menu changed from "After 20 mins" to "Never".

event: The mouse clicked on After 5 hours.
description: The user clicked on "After 5 hours" in the "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu.  As a result, the "Turn off monitor" setting changed from "After 20 mins" to "After 5 hours".
outcome: The "Turn off monitor" setting within the "Settings for Home/Office Desk power scheme" section changed from "After 20 mins" to "Never".

description: The user clicked the "OK" button at the bottom of the "Power Options Properties" window. As a result, the "Power Options Properties" window closed.
outcome: The "Power Options Properties" window is not visible in this frame.
